diffgram/labels/tiff","name":"tiff","color":"22133E","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2022-02-18T22:18:57Z","updated_at":"2022-03-03T03:08:22Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"### When?\r\nWhen we do the DICOM interface, it could be the first one for example that we build native support for layers.\r\nOr can start with TIFF in the images case.\r\nOr ?\r\n\r\n### Frontend\r\nIn frontend provide UI to switch between multiple assets for the same file.\r\nThis can be with canvas, e.g. background image a `v-for`.\r\nAnd go with best standard from photoshop or similar for UI exp switching between layers.\r\n\r\n### Backend\r\nIn backend provide storage support for multiple presentation layer assets on the same file.\r\n\r\nOne way to approach this would be to support linking a series of elements to one file. \r\nFor example adding `file.image_id_list` or something in that direction.\r\nThat way all the concerns regarding storage URLs, previews, etc etc would be handled.\r\n\r\nIf that was too intensive (e.g. 1000s of layers per file) we can use the \"naming convention only\" approach with video\r\n\r\n### Both\r\n1. Add which layer the instance is on in `instance`\r\n\r\n### Applies to:\r\n1. DICOM\r\n2. TIFF\r\n3. Geospatial\r\n4. Images\r\n5. ?\r\n\r\n\r\nThis is a very rough sketch\r\n","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/diffgram/diffgram/issues/637/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/diffgram/diffgram/issues/637/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}